Ask HN: Is there a “Yelp for SaaS software/platforms”?
text:
Is there is a “Yelp for SaaS”? (Or replace SaaS with any of “cloud”, “platform”, etc)

I hypothesize that lots of time and effort is being duplicated by teams migrating an integration and wasting a lot of time before realizing a service has severe drawbacks. My most recent project was to integrate AWS Cognito (authentication solution) a few years ago before aspects of it were very immature for customer-facing purposes.

It’s easy to find lots of PR / sales material that focuses on the positive side of platforms (the 5 star reviews). I’m more interested in collecting the 1-3 star reviews as they can help identify likely pitfalls before investing too much hope in one implementation.

Show HN: Morse Code Camera
text:
I made an IOS app for transmitting Morse code through the flashlight and decoding Morse code through the camera. I had the idea a while ago and didn't see any decent implementations so I decided to have a go at it. Let me know what you think!

There is also an Android app https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.wpeery.mor.... However, it is a bit less polished as it was the one I ended up making first. I may go back and update it to be more inline with the IOS app if I get the time.

Ask HN: What's Shipping?
text:
How clear are exec teams and product leads at your company about what is shipping and when?

If they know, how do they know? Project management tools don't give you a clear sense of what's shipping and when.

How often do you have to answer questions of the nature "hey, when is that thing shipping?", "what's shipping in this next release?" etc.
